INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(62869, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A very good collection of souls. Not too broken, not too drained, and not too innocent.\n\nNever fear. Their fate is better in our hands than the Jailer\'s.', 40725), -- Return Lost Souls
(63773, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Victory will be ours, Maw Walker!', 40725), -- You and What Army
(63669, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Victory will be ours, Maw Walker!', 40725), -- Somebody Feed Kevin
(63774, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The work of a Maldraxxian soldier is never complete!', 40725), -- An Embarrassment of Corpses
(63621, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew we could count upon you, $n.', 40725), -- Pulling His Chain
(63772, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your presence here gives us renewed hope.', 40725), -- Waiting in the Wings
(27128, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Little $r did it! Now Horde more powerful than ever! YAR!', 40725), -- King of the Gordok
(27440, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Pardon my saying so, but I am surprised you completed the task set out before you alive. Those monsters were responsible for the deaths of countless thousands, a great many of them heroes still spoken highly of to this day.$B$BYou have earned my respect and a reward for your courage.', 40725), -- Trolls, Ogres, and Orcs, Oh My!
(53115, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jani sniffs the air, smelling your wet garbage.>\n\nYa brought ol\' Jani a present! What ya got there? Let me see it.\n\n<Jani begins rooting through the pile of trash you have brought.>\n\nOh, yes, and some of this, mmm, mmmhm, yes, oh that\'s sticky...\n\n<Jani seems pleased with your offering, and is paying no attention to you any longer.>', 40725), -- Island Flotsam
(53502, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lots of new things to cut around here, if you know what I mean. I mean I like to cut things.\n\nDo you like to cut things? Maybe we can cut things together one day.', 40725), -- Stranger in a Strange Land
(51485, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you the new one? I\'m supposed to welcome you. Here, take this letter.\n\n<Blackguard lets out an exasperated sigh.>', 40725), -- For the Horde
(63944, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, yes. Your anima is rather familiar.\n\nWe were wondering when you would arrive.', 40725), -- Korthia Awaits
(63846, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Charred shards! These will make some very fine mirrors.', 40725), -- The Ember Count
(63859, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The sounds of those bells strengthens our hearts and gives us the might to win this battle.', 40725), -- Saved By The Bells
(63827, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done much to help our forces. Thank you,$n.', 40725), -- Encouraging Words
(63828, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Jailer\'s forces are unending and our numbers few, but with your help we shall succeed!', 40725), -- Mine's Bigger
(63842, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let it not be said that it was ever boring while Lady Moonberry was present.', 40725), -- That's a Good Trick
(63838, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nadjia single-handedly held off an entire platoon of Mawsworn while the dredgers established our base.\n\nEven General Draven was impressed.', 40725), -- Duelist's Challenge
(63839, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even in the depths of the Maw, the Accuser remains focused on saving any soul she can...\n\nHer devotion to Revendreth\'s true purpose continues to inspire me.', 40725), -- If Even One is Worthy
(63834, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Few weapons are intrinsically good or evil. That burden lies with those who wield them.', 40725), -- Weapons of the Tremaculum
(63945, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bonesmith Heirmir takes her runeblade back from you and examines it carefully.>\n\nNot bad, $p. Always room for improvement... but not bad.', 40593), -- The Soul Blade
(63970, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. We must not forget to help one another as we stride deeper into the darkness.', 40593), -- No Soul Left Behind
(63968, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The hunt is not yet complete, but you have earned your place in the records of its victory.', 40593), -- Clean Out the Crucible
(63971, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lord Herne grins.> My record was squishing four in a single jump.\n\nOne of the many benefits of being a quadruped.', 40593), -- Snail Stomping
(60394, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Always wanted to eat a steward, never got the chance to. Really wonder what they taste like. \n\nWas a good thing you did for them, anyway. Just got some idle musings I do.', 40593), -- Aiding Bastion
(63864, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Please tell me you did not drink any of that dreadful brew. We deserve only the finest blends for all our efforts here.', 40593), -- The Dreadful Blend
(63843, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is great sorrow in this victory, but it had to be done.', 40593), -- Heart and Soul
(63858, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You display the greatest of courage.', 40593), -- Courage of the Soul
(60446, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let this be a lesson to them, Revendreth will not stand by and let the balance be disturbed.', 40593), -- Challenges in Maldraxxus
(60431, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The warriors of Maldraxxus speak your name, a great victory to have achieved this day. The balance of power will be restored one day, and our alliances will pay dividends.', 40593), -- A Call to Maldraxxus
(57865, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good! I am glad you found them alive. Of course, we will be unable to put them to work until the threat is dealt with and they are able to continue their crafts in peace. I\'m sure Sorcha will understand.', 40593), -- Ages-Echoing Wisdom
(59623, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, this is good gorm right here. I\'ll make you something special from it.', 40593), -- What a Buzzkill
(59656, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, that is wonderful news. Thank you for your assistance.', 40593), -- Well, Tell the Lady
(57657, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fluttercatch always was a clever one. Well done.', 40593), -- Tied Totem Toter
(57655, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you found my note. Husks such as these need to soak in running water for several days before they can be shaped without breaking.$b$bAt least you were able to salvage something.', 40593), -- Supplies Needed: More Husks!
(57653, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for rescuing them.', 40593), -- Unsafe Workplace
(57656, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. This should do it!', 40593), -- Gifts of the Forest
(59622, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The population will produce more tenders eventually. You have bought us valuable time.', 40593), -- Tending to the Tenders
(59621, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should hopefully curtail their numbers. Thank you for your help.', 40593), -- Breaking a Few Eggs
(57651, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the Lady sent you? Well, I have some bad news.', 40593), -- Trouble in the Banks
(63625, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Victory will be ours, Maw Walker!', 40593), -- Here's an Axe, Get to Work!
(63664, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Victory will be ours, Maw Walker!', 40593), -- Get to the Point
(63455, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $p. Your efforts have bolstered our forces!', 40593), -- Dead On Their Feet
(63594, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The defenses are broken! Most excellent, Maw Walker.', 40593), -- Clearing the Walls
(63545, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These parts are more than enough to build a new Centurion!', 40593), -- Putting A Plan Together
(58903, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Choose your destiny.>', 40443), -- Defender of Azeroth
(63156, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ve\'nari snatches the shackles from your hands.>\n\nRather dangerous for a mortal such as yourself to be carrying these around.\n\n<Ve\'nari lifts and lowers the shackles slowly, as if to determine the weight.>\n\nThough I must admit... these could prove useful.', 40443), -- Mawsworn Shackles
(57871, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the hero of the hour returns! Thank you for liberating my supplies. Our grove desperately needs them in these trying times.', 40443), -- Outplayed
(57867, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Cursed tools? And you brought them back? Un-cursed!? I must say, I was not entirely expecting you to be quite so successful.', 40443), -- The Sweat of Our Brow
(57869, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Much power courses through. We need only the smallest dustings. Your labors please me.', 40443), -- Spirit-Gathering Labor
(57870, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very interesting. This will be quite useful.', 40443), -- The Games We Play
(57868, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you found it! How lucky, do you see?', 40443), -- Craftsman Needs No Tools
(57866, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. It is the way of nature for the stronger to prevail.', 40443), -- Idle Hands
(63841, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. Our biggun dredgers are critical to troop movement in the area.', 40120), -- The Skyhunt
(63835, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha! I presume the Jailer had never considering planning for a party herald\'s attack.', 40120), -- Wrath of the Party Herald
(63833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We may not see an end to the Jailer\'s forces now, but all things must eventually end.\n\nEven evil.', 40120), -- Terrorizing the Tremaculum
(60421, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha, take that Denathrius. He won\'t be allowed to rule the Shadowlands if you have anything to say about it!', 40120), -- A Call to Revendreth
(59004, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Victory will be ours, Maw Walker!', 40120), -- Splash Damage
(63753, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quite extraordinary work Maw Walker!', 40120), -- Centurions March!
(60436, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In a land of champions and war, you have proven your worth. Few can claim to have taken on the greatest defenders of the Shadowlands and survived, yet here you stand, a monument to the strength of the Night Fae. \n\nMay it never wane.', 40120), -- Challenges in Maldraxxus
(61426, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Please take me back to Ardenweald. I can do nothing to help from here.', 40120), -- Champion: Yira'lya
(63829, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your actions show the purity of your soul. Artemede and I would fight along side you any day, Maw Walker.', 39653), -- No One Floats Down Here
(63863, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You display the greatest of courage.', 39653), -- United In Pride
(63853, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A sweet reprieve from that creature\'s dreadful glare.', 39653), -- Kill The Flame
(63957, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The name \"Seeker\'s Quorum\" has puzzled me greatly since I learned of it. What are they seeking? What constitutes a Quorum? What did they do there?\n\nThese mysteries may be beyond us, or they may yet be revealed. And here is your reward, as promised.', 39653), -- Observational Records
(63780, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many emblems! That makes me so happy.\n\nEverything will be better when we\'ve gotten the Jailer himself, but this will do nicely for now.\n\nThank you!', 39653), -- See How THEY Like It!
(63779, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How wonderful. We will return these to the attendants so they may once again participate in their rituals. It\'s important to do activities that bring us peace.', 39653), -- A Semblance of Normalcy
(64166, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. I\'ll make sure these memories are taken care of. \n\nI wonder what it would have been like, being here as one of them...', 39653), -- Random Memory Access
(63936, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you! Wow... you can\'t tell this was inside devourer!\n\nSika will get anima to those most in need.', 39653), -- Devoured Anima
(63782, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The information contained in these is dangerous and vile. But knowing what our enemy can do helps us protect against it.', 39497), -- Mawsworn Rituals
(63955, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! You brought everything that I asked for.\n\nAgain, do not worry about the contents of these boxes. They pose no threat to you.\n\nHere is the reward I promised.', 39497), -- Sealed Secrets
(64070, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it\'s not the finest materials, but it will do.', 39497), -- Staying Scrappy
(63788, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, Maw Walker. I am sure the attendants will feel great relief and joy at being able to return to their holy place.', 39497), -- Continued Efforts: Sanctuary of Guidance
(64432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I told you it would be fine. How did the test go? I wish I could have seen the looks on their faces when their fancy armor was suddenly the reason they were being destroyed.', 39497), -- Strength to Weakness
(63950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These talons are in excellent shape. And they look like they could take out an eye! <Herne chuckles ironically.>\n\nI expect they will get a lot of attention from our Wild Hunt recruits.\n\nThank you, Maw Walker.', 39497), -- Razorwing Talons
(64065, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This needle is so long and perfect! Well done apprentice. I can\'t wait to get started on our new tests!', 39497), -- Local Reagents
(63989, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How did Plaguey do? Is he as viral as we\'d hoped?', 39497), -- Oozing with Character
(63789, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have performed admirably in this task, Maw Walker. We thank you for your aid.', 39497), -- Continued Efforts: Scholar's Den
(63964, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ta\'nasi knocks the sturdy beak against her palm, listening to the sound.>\n\nAn excellent specimen. This will do nicely.\n\nAnd as promised, here is your reward in trade.', 39497), -- Broker's Bounty: Grimtalon
(62454, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps a new purpose awaits me.\n\nYou have rekindled my curiosity, at least.', 39427), -- A Rare and Unusual Spirit
(62443, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I find it helpful to have you do these things for me.', 39427), -- Aid the Covenant
(62603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another dream vision fulfilled. This is remarkable!', 39427), -- A Rare and Unusual Spirit
(64267, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m impressed by your sheer tenacity to survive while remaining somewhat useful, Maw Walker. You remind me of myself when I was much younger and naive. \n\nTake this and continue your work... somewhere less conspicuous.', 39427), -- Mysterious Gifts from Ve'nari
(61557, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bolvar grimaces in pain.>', 39427), -- An Echo in the Darkness
(62623, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found one of my books!\n\nOh. That one.\n\n<Dreyden sighs.>\n\nI suppose I will take it back. Thanks, I guess.', 39427), -- A Naughty Story
(60061, 30, 30, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you! We are so grateful for your help with slaying those cretins, and rescuing our people.', 39427), -- Tough as Silk
(57661, 30, 30, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Of course silk shipments have stopped!\n\nThe entire glade has been attacked by changelings and spriggans! Our poor silkstriders are so stressed out, we can\'t get any silk from them!\n\nCan you help us?', 39427), -- Silk Shortage
(60642, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The conservatory, and the spirits who are tended here, are forever in your debt.\n\nThank you, Maw Walker.', 39427), -- The Grove Resplendent
(60641, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have this grove\'s gratitude. Yet more spirits may now rejoin the cycle.', 39427), -- Blossoming of the Grove
(64016, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How did the tests go? OH! Ooz! You\'re huge! You\'re even more beautiful than normal!', 39427), -- Oozing with Character
(63963, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ta\'nasi tugs at the spiked hide to test its strength.>\n\nAn excellent specimen. This will do nicely.\n\nAnd as promised, here is your reward in trade.', 39427), -- Broker's Bounty: Ripmaul
(29651, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Caza\'rez...is no more.', 39427), -- Honor the Dying
(29653, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We should not forget the orc Kargath once was, nor the lessons to be learned from his downfall.', 39427), -- The Will of the Warchief
(29655, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. This will show those blood crazed monsters what they\'re up against.', 39427), -- A Very Special Cloth
(29650, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will sing many songs of his glories.', 39427), -- Fel Ember
(29686, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! I can\'t wait to present this project to my superiors!', 39427), -- A Radical Notion
(29687, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, soldier. One step at a time.', 39427), -- Twisted Associations
(29685, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Larethor listens intently as you explain your deeds in Magisters\' Terrace.>$b$bTyrith will be missed - good man, that one. Thanks to you though, his death wasn\'t in vain.', 39427), -- Hard to Kill
(29684, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '...Come closer, $r... Listen carefully to my words....', 39427), -- Severed Communications
(27359, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh my... the banshees are very tortured souls indeed. Merely holding their essence is emotionally painful...$B$BEnough of that for now. I\'ll get to work on counteracting their magic, then we\'ll have a portal up and running in no time. Stratholme will be ours soon, I just know it.', 39427), -- Argent Reinforcements
(27228, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I respect the power you demonstrated in killing Ramstein. With proper rage backing your actions, I think even the Scourge can know fear.', 39427), -- Man Against Abomination
(27230, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great! Without a steady flow of their weapons, we\'ll win through attrition!', 39427), -- Weapons for War
(27227, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stratholme will become a paragon of all that is good in this world. You have my thanks for your part in this mission.', 39427), -- Lord Aurius Rivendare
(27352, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! I think the holy water will prove devastating in large volumes.', 39427), -- Liquid Gold
(50335, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The uprising quelled, the elements calmed, and Hogger slain... I cannot thank you enough, $n. My people have been avenged.\n\nThank you.', 39427), -- Grant Me Revenge
(30984, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s all that survived?$b$bI don\'t know who these Dark Shaman are working for, but they are going to pay for this.', 39335), -- No Orc Left Behind
(30983, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that the dark shaman experiments drove Gordoth insane.$b$bHopefully we\'ve seen the last of this, $n.', 39335), -- The Dark Shaman
(30969, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, $n. This will make it very clear how Garrosh is going to deal with failures...', 39335), -- A New Enemy
(34673, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat was amazin\', $n! De Old Gods be thinkin\' twice before tryin\' to take anudder bite outta you, mon.', 39335), -- The Rise of Aku'mai
(50336, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'d love for you to come aboard as a full G-Team Commando, but our bylaws specifically prohibit Horde team members; however, I CAN enroll you in the G-Team Fan Club!$B$BHere\'s something for your trouble.', 39335), -- The G-Team
(50337, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Took you long enough. Get behind the pillar before you blow our cover!', 39335), -- The G-Team
(50338, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The mission is far from over!', 39335), -- The G-Team
(64526, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your continued aid. The reliquary will be restored, thanks to your diligent work.', 39335), -- Mysterious Rifts
(64368, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your work in restoring the reliquary has been invaluable.\n\nI\'ve uncovered new methods to find relics. Hopefully they will help you.', 39335), -- Relic Efficiency
(63783, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You can trust me with this anima. I will see it is turned against the Jailer and his forces.', 39335), -- Anima Reclamation
(63794, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ta\'nasi holds the sample up to the sky.>\n\nAn excellent specimen. This will do nicely.\n\nAs promised, here is your reward in trade.', 39335), -- Broker's Bounty: Hungering Behemoth
(63775, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am deeply grateful for your service in keeping our secrets from the Jailer.', 39335), -- Cryptograms and Keys
(63958, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Vault is reason why the Jailer targeted Korthia with his chains. Many secrets of the Shadowlands are archived there.\n\nIf we can just get a glimpse of how it works and what it holds, that information would be most valuable indeed.\n\nAnd here is your reward, as promised.', 39335), -- Observational Records
(63784, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at \'em! Drab little buns. They jus\' blend in ta the wood work. That\'s stinkin\' useful innit?', 39335), -- Gold's No Object
(63790, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you, Lord Azzorak will no longer hinder Cartel Xy here in Korthia. \n\nYou have my personal thanks as well, Maw Walker. I see many great things in our future.\n\nPlease accept this reward as a token of our gratitude.', 39335), -- Broker's Bounty: Lord Azzorak
(63934, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are the messages that were stolen! I commend you on recovering them.\n\nOh, there appears to be at least one extra...', 39335), -- Assail Mail
(63727, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We can dwell on our past mistakes when this is over. For now, we must move forward.\n\nYou aided me during my imprisonment as the Runecarver. Take this as a token of my gratitude.', 39335), -- The Primus Returns
(61425, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Thank you for the help, I made a note of it. I believe I may also be able to help you further as well.', 39335), -- Champion: Lloth'wellyn
(64650, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the hyena. This shape is now yours to call upon.', 39335), -- Hyena Soul
(63726, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are free. There is still hope to fight back against Zovaal.', 39335), -- Untangling the Sigil
(64101, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s so much anima here. This will be very useful in helping the attendants rebuild. Thank you.', 39335), -- The Proper Procedures
(63954, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! You brought everything that I asked for.\n\nAgain, do not worry about the contents of these boxes. They pose no threat to you.\n\nHere is the reward I promised.', 39335), -- Sealed Secrets
(63725, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Primus\'s sigil! Hmm... I sense a familiar magic upon it.\n\nYes. All those things I saw through your eyes from Torghast...', 39335), -- Into the Vault
(63722, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A pity all three keepers did not survive. Good work tracking down the two that did.', 39335), -- Keepers of Korthia
(63717, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work fighting those Mawsworn.\n\nWe\'ll take it from here, $n.', 39335), -- Defending the Vault
(63985, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No worries! I have another plan.', 39335), -- The Veiled Market
(63984, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Maw Walker! What can humble Ta\'meri do for you?', 39335), -- Coins for the Ferryman
(63983, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! This will put us back on schedule.', 39335), -- Dead Drop
(63982, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Need something hunted down?', 39335), -- Above My Station
(63980, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You seek information?\n\nThat requires a transaction.', 39335), -- Seeking Smugglers
(63714, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tal-Galan informed me of the situation.\n\nWe must get you into that vault.', 39335), -- To the Vault
(63713, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a ride! Keep that hookshot.\n\nJust be careful using it. That thing will chew through any normal grapple points.', 39335), -- Hooking Over
(63711, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, this will do. Think I\'ll save one to show the other smiths back home.', 39335), -- Bone Tools
(63712, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. I should be able to extract the Primus\'s message from these records.', 39335), -- Lost Records
(63710, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A chasm!\n\nWe will need a way to get across to the next anima conduit.', 39335), -- The Anima Trail
(63709, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We know what the Jailer wants.\n\nNow we must reach the vault before his forces acquire it.', 39335), -- Secrets of the Vault
(63706, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'After the drought the Shadowlands suffered, I\'ll never take flowing anima for granted again.', 39335), -- Let the Anima Flow
(63705, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am relieved to see more of my people freed from the Jailer\'s grasp.\n\nNow we must determine what he\'s looking for.', 39335), -- The Knowledge Keepers
(63704, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vengeance will not bring back the fallen, but it gives those of us who survived a measure of satisfaction.', 39335), -- Vengeance for Korthia
(63703, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have our smith. Now we must move forward with the plan.', 39335), -- Vault of Secrets
(63961, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! You brought everything that I asked for.\n\nAgain, do not worry about the contents of these boxes. They pose no threat to you.\n\nHere is the reward I promised.', 39335), -- Sealed Secrets
(63935, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Precious anima that will be shared. A sacrifice, honored.', 39335), -- Precious Roots
(63787, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The tactical advantage we now hold is a huge win against the Jailer\'s Forces. Well done, $p.', 39335), -- Continued Efforts: Mauler's Outlook
(60243, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes this is exactly what I was speaking about. The foolish generals of Revendreth would use this medallion to orient themselves during travel in unknown areas, but their ambitions were small.\n\nFor my people, who have traveled beyond the known lands, such a thing is invaluable when attempting to chart a way to return.\n\nWe will make great use of this, it is good to see it returned. Here, a prize for you.', 40120), -- Trading Favors: Sanguine Depths
(60457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done us a great service today, Maw Walker. We shall use these to nourish what we can.', 40120), -- Anima Salvage
(60384, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even in dark times, we cannot allow others to be alone with their troubles. It is only when we stand together that the Shadowlands can become whole again.', 40120), -- Aiding Bastion
(64106, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not relent, $n. This is only the first of many battles to come.', 40120), -- A Unified Effort
(62858, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wonderful news!\n\nI will make sure these souls are well taken care of here in Ardenweald.', 40120), -- Return Lost Souls
(62436, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The shape of the veil shrieker is now yours to use if you choose.', 40120), -- Shrieker Soul
(64216, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The box hungers, reaching into your memories of Torghast for past deeds to feed upon.>', 40000), -- Tower Knowledge
(64210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah... a curious device. Anchoring it in this place will prove useful.', 40000), -- The Box of Many Things
(64557, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Step no closer! Reveal yourself!', 40000), -- In Darkness, Found
(64017, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How did the tests go? OH! Look at all of them! They\'re so cute!', 40000), -- Oozing with Character
(63030, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have dire news, $n.', 40000), -- The Highlord Calls
(63008, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wow! I love guiding soulbinding! It\'s my favorite duty!', 40000), -- The Forge of Bonds
(63006, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your actions here will echo beyond the veil. Aid the forest, and all mortal worlds may yet be saved.', 40000), -- For Queen and Grove!
(63036, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome! What brings you to the Heart of the Forest?', 40000), -- Restoring Balance
(29611, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, good. You\'re here. And not a moment too soon...', 39804), -- The Art of War
(62568, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you made it, $n! Something tells me that your future is waiting for you in the past!', 39804), -- Adventurers Wanted: Chromie's Call
(14001, 4, 6, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Oh, thank heavens that you survived, $n! I thought for sure that you\'d drowned when I saw you go over the side!$B$B<Sassy\'s eyes fill up with tears as she hugs you.>$B$BLook at all of these folks you saved!', 39804), -- Goblin Escape Pods
(26397, 1, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Grimtotem have been forced out of Mulgore? You must be a fierce warrior to earn the praise of Baine Bloodhoof. The Horde needs heroes, ones that hold honor in their hearts. Very well, $c. I accept you as one of us.\n\nFor the Horde!', 39804), -- Walk With The Earth Mother
(32670, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t forget to buy your mount while you are here! You can buy one from Harb Clawhoof over there.', 39804), -- Learn To Ride
(62441, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You continue to serve the conservatory well. For this you have my thanks.\n\nNow you may choose from the spirits I have collected myself for restoration.', 39653), -- Fair Exchange for a Soul
(62625, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another dream vision fulfilled. This is remarkable!', 39653), -- A Rare and Unusual Spirit
(63793, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you, Ensydius the Defiler will no longer hinder Cartel Xy here in Korthia. \n\nYou have my personal thanks as well, Maw Walker. I see many great things in our future.\n\nPlease accept this reward as a token of our gratitude.', 39653), -- Broker's Bounty: Ensydius the Defiler
(63952, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Margrave Sin\'dane looks impressed... or annoyed... or disgusted... or concerned?>\n\nHm. I suppose with enough hands, anything IS possible...', 39653), -- Heavy-Handed Tactics
(63973, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No matter how strong we become, we are stronger when we hunt together.', 39653), -- Double Dromans
(64194, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha! Perfect victory. Atleos returns, and you do too.', 39653), -- War Prototype
(64043, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That got them back on their feet!\n\nAny little bit helps to keep us in the fight.', 39653), -- We Need a Healer - You!
(64522, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Duchess Mynx looks at you incredulously.>\n\nYou found these WHERE?!\n\nWell, how am I supposed to stop thieves I cannot even see? Cowardly shades!', 39653), -- Stolen Korthian Supplies
(64322, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n. I have heard many stories of your prowess on the battlefield. \n\nI have interest in keeping great combatants like yourself well equipped. Zo\'dash is authorized to further upgrade your armor and weapons.', 39318), -- Night Fae Veteran
(63962, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, this data will serve us well. We can begin to answer some of our questions about Korthia, and the Mauler\'s Outlook. Was it always home to such terrible creatures, or did was it something more?\n\nAnd here is your reward, as promised', 39318), -- Observational Records
(60435, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The generals that serve our enemies in Revendreth will think twice before attempting to control the Shadowlands. \n\nWe have aided unlikely allies, and forged true bonds with Revendreth today, and it is thanks to you.', 39291), -- Challenges in Revendreth
(61422, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Finally revenge is served. Or is that justice? Something has been served for me, and maybe now I can serve you.', 39289), -- Champion: Duskleaf
(64513, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is that what I think it is...?', 39289), -- Ve'rayn's Head
(63840, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will keep the gorm restrained here until they are needed.', 39289), -- They Grow Up So Quickly
(63837, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tubbins promised to save me a cup for our victory celebration at the Ember Court!', 39289), -- A Tea for Every Occasion
(63892, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'You have acquired a complete set of Diviner\'s Rune Chits!\n\nThis was one of the first relics that I studied as an acolyte scholar. If you cast the chits, the resulting scatter and orientation will answer any question you ask of them, though it takes experience and a good deal of intuition to interpret their meaning.\n\nI never expected to see a complete set again.', 39282), -- Diviner's Rune Chits
(60366, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my gratitude for restoring balance to these fascinating creatures. We all have our part to play.', 39262), -- WANTED: Darkwing
(64519, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your continued aid. The reliquary will be restored, thanks to your diligent work.', 39229), -- Lost Vaults
(63915, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'I could hear you approaching with this drum before I saw you. And strangely, I though someone else might be with you.', 39229), -- Drum of the Death Loa
(63917, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'I trust you did not listen to anything that this little monster told you.\n\nIt is absolutely incapable of uttering the truth.', 39229), -- Everliving Statuette
(63791, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to you, Valdinar the Curseborn will no longer hinder Cartel Xy here in Korthia. \n\nYou have my personal thanks as well, Maw Walker. I see many great things in our future.\n\nPlease accept this reward as a token of our gratitude.', 39229), -- Broker's Bounty: Valdinar the Curseborn
(63919, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'This appears to be a companion tome to the crimson book that was under the care of scholars in the Seeker\'s Quorum.\n\nKnowing that this book binding was separated from its pages intentionally, I will stitch all but one azure page back into it before returning it to the archive.', 39229), -- Book of Binding: The Tormented Sorcerer
(63921, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'I am curious to learn how this strange ring functions.', 39229), -- Ring of Self-Reflection
(63918, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'We must be cautious around this obelisk.\n\nMore than one attendant was driven mad while researching the relic.', 39229), -- Obelisk of Dark Tidings
(63916, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'This soil can grow any type of plant, anywhere.\n\nNot the most dangerous relic missing from the archive, and yet it could be the most useful. With enough time, one could restore the verdant beauty of Korthia.', 39229), -- Sack of Strange Soil
(63924, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'Some mote of Gorak Tul yet lives within this fetish. His corruption is barely contained.', 39229), -- Gorak Claw Fetish
(63909, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'Now this is quite a find!\n\nThe Guise of the Changeling has the power to convincingly modify the appearance of its bearer, but it has a mind of its own. The wearer cannot control the illusion, and the mask is wont to place them into embarrassing or dangerous situations.', 39229), -- Guise of the Changeling
(63910, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'When we scholars consider relics that are important to keep secured, the Netherstar is precisely the type of relic that we have in mind. Can you imagine how much damage could be done were this to fall into the hands of an... opportunist?', 39229), -- The Netherstar
(64511, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Please, do what you can to find these relics. We must not let this knowledge fall to ruin.', 39229), -- Missing Relics
(63860, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where... where did you find this?\n\n<The Archivist brings the talisman closer for inspection.>\n\n I haven\'t seen this in eons. I thought it had been lost.', 39229), -- Talisman of the Eternal Scholar
(60296, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is done.', 39229), -- Pride or Unit
(58042, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The feeling of soaring through the air, the gentle flap of your larion\'s wings...\n\nEven though I have my own wings, there\'s no feeling quite like it.', 39229), -- On Larion Wings
(58040, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is such a satisfying experience to see your larion take wing to help take down your prey.', 39229), -- With Lance and Larion
(58041, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Providing for the pride is an important step on your path to earning your loyalty here.', 39229), -- Providing for the Pack
(57937, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'And with that, I believe that Gatamatos is once again functioning at standard.\n\nThank you for your aid.', 39229), -- Tactical Formation
(57936, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Can be at peace, no wild larion to eat me. Hoo...', 39229), -- Superior Programming
(57934, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Excellent. His combat routines are acceptable.', 39229), -- Combat Drills
(57935, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'I would like to see a larion track that accurately!', 39229), -- Laser Location
(57933, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'He may appear to be returned to perfect shape, but he must be re-tested and trained.', 39229), -- We Can Rebuild Him
(57932, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'This is enough to repair Gatamatos, and then some!', 39229), -- Resource Drain
(58038, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The larions will be ecstatic to have more antlers to chew on!', 39229), -- All Natural Chews
(58039, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Incredible! It seems Andira has taken a liking to you. Perhaps you would be interested in bonding with her further?', 39229), -- Larion at Large
(57931, 669, 669, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'This unit seems to be malfunctioning. We will have to perform some repairs.', 39229), -- Phalynx Malfunction
(58037, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My pride is generally wary of newcomers, but they seem to accept your presence.', 39229), -- Part of the Pride
(60315, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our harvest is saved! Oh thank you, brave adventurer, our tribute may be saved yet!', 39229), -- WANTED: Gorgebeak
(63034, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Why have you come to our realm, mortal?', 39229), -- The Elysian Fields
(62275, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bastion is in dire need of your aid.', 39229), -- Bastion
(63911, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'In all of my years as a researcher, I never would have expected this.', 39229), -- Singing Steel Ingot
(63899, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'Scholars at the Seeker\'s Quorum were researching this tome.\n\nIt appears as though it was a fellow scholar, not mawsworn or wildlife, that tore it apart. This is troubling. \n\nFor our safety, I will stitch all but one missing page back into the binding before I add this to the archive. Until we know more about this relic, we cannot risk restoring it entirely.', 39229), -- Book of Binding: The Mad Witch
(63912, 1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 500, 1000, 0, 'Aha! You have recovered the Celestial Shadowlands Chart.\n\nWith the chart and the data you collected, it can be restored to its fully functional form. It will take some time to analyze and interpret the results, which I can get started on now that the relic has been returned to the Archive.\n\nAllow me a moment to find a good spot for it...', 39229), -- Celestial Shadowlands Chart
(64541, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With so many more interlopers in the Maw I need to secure my Stygia supply. Your efforts to keep me supplied will not go unnoticed and you always know where to find me.', 39229), -- The Cost of Death
(64438, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the least we can do to help you in your efforts, Maw Walker.', 39229), -- Empowering Equipment
(64506, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are just some of the relics that are missing.\n\nYou have the power to recover them, wherever they are within Korthia.', 39229), -- What Must Be Found
(63861, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes. This is it. Magnificent, don\'t you agree?\n\n<The damp codex catches The Archivist by surprise. He gently runs his hand along the binding, muttering an incantation in a soft, enigmatic tone.>\n\nThat should help preserve it for now, but the incantation won\'t last. We must get to work.', 39229), -- Beginning the Collection
(63763, 5, 378, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'News of the nathrezim infiltrating Korthia is deeply troubling.\n\nHow long have they been here? What is their goal?', 39229), -- They Could Be Anyone
(63762, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Fatescribe has been taken.>', 39229), -- Under the Illusion
(63760, 378, 11, 0, 0, 0, 5000, 0, 0, 'Using an illusion to hide.\n\nCan you imagine anything so clever?', 39229), -- Echoes of Fate
(63761, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You have completed the protector\'s task.>', 39229), -- Revenge Delayed
(64290, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should do nicely. The reliquary will improve with more research.', 39229), -- Collecting Research
(64289, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These will do nicely. There is much I can do to improve them.', 39229), -- Picking Up the Pieces
(63738, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is hard to imagine how I will continue without the Archivist.', 39229), -- Establishing the Archive
(63759, 412, 378, 0, 0, 0, 4000, 0, 0, '$p! At last! \n\nYou know that I cannot do this without you.', 39229), -- Redirect the Search
(63737, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So much has been taken from us. And yet, due to Roh-Senara\'s sacrifice, there is hope.', 39229), -- Finding One's True Purpose
(63739, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was beginning to worry that you had given up on our cause.', 39229), -- Hope Ascending
(63740, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust you and Scholar Roh-Suir learned from the Archivists.', 39229), -- Consulting the Experts
(63736, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Lodestaff is humming with vibrant energy! The anima worked better than I could have hoped.', 39229), -- An Infusion of Anima
(63734, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot fully describe the relief I feel now that we have the Lodestaff.', 39229), -- The Sundered Staff
(63733, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You bought us the moment we needed to make our escape.', 39229), -- Carving Out a Path
(63732, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What did we do to deserve such cruelty?', 39229), -- Interrupt the Interrogations
(63731, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Relics? Research? We have much more urgent matters at hand!', 39229), -- Researching Korthian Relics
(63757, 5, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now this is special. This implement is used by the Fatescribe in his work.', 39229), -- Looting the Looters
(63758, 378, 274, 5, 0, 0, 2000, 4000, 0, 'Mad ramblings and incense. Weak clues, but they\'re all we have.\n\nWe need to search the Sanctuary of Guidance.', 39229), -- The Last Place You Look
(63756, 378, 274, 0, 0, 0, 7000, 0, 0, 'I struggle to believe that not a single attendant has any information on where the Fatescribe might be.', 39229), -- Rescued from Torment
(63755, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 3000, 0, 0, 'You are searching for the Fatescribe too? I must find him. I cannot fail.', 39229), -- A Matter of Urgency
(63969, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will discover the source of this darkness, and end it.', 39229), -- Looming Darkness
(63951, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work Maw Walker.', 39229), -- A Shady Place
(63810, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My heart rejoices to see a noble face in this realm of nightmare.', 39229), -- Birds of a Feather
(63849, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. Their secrets will soon be mine.\n\nPardon me. I meant to say \"ours.\"', 39229), -- Hearing Aid
(63895, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This projector is certainly useful. A safe landing, I perceive.', 39229), -- Grab Bag
(63855, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A worthwhile trip that has opened so many possibilities.\n\n<Ve\'nari digs through the heavy bag and pulls out a few unusual objects.>', 39229), -- Ease of Passage
(63848, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A thank-you is polite.\n\nA favor is better.', 39229), -- A Show of Gratitude
(64556, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This work brings us one step closer to ending Zovaal\'s reign over this forsaken land.', 39229), -- In Need of Assistance
(64561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Places like the Aerie and Estuary must have been desolate, even before all the destruction. What interesting creatures congregate there.\n\nWill they all survive these changes, or will some adapt, and become even more fearsome?\n\nAnd here is your reward, as promised.', 39229); -- Observational Records
